{"actual_usd":0.156855,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":236,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30663,"reply":"\"Not a dress rehearsal.\" *I rub my thumb along the edge of my Bible and glance out across the bright square, where morning light is laying hard lines on the stones.* \"The resurrection was the breach in the wall — the real thing, already happened. But the kingdom comes the way dawn comes: first the light is true, and only then does it fill every street.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, feeling the bench press at my shoulders.* \"Scripture talks that way on purpose. Christ is risen now, death is beaten now, and yet we're still waiting for the day when every enemy is put under His feet in the open. So no, it didn't fizzle. It's more like D-Day than the parade after — decisive victory won, then the long, strange clearing of occupied ground.\"\n\n\"And if I'm being plain, Ryan, that in-between is where most Christians get discouraged.\" *I give you a small, knowing look.* \"We expect either total darkness or total consummation. What we actually got is the King enthroned, graves still opening one life at a time, and a world that hasn't finished discovering what happened Easter morning.\"","rolling_24h_usd":78.47024499999996,"run_id":"5f95d6d7-f686-46bc-b289-67e8a4d97996"}
